         <entryFree xml:id="k000087" type="site type">
            <term xml:id="term-k000087-1" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin-nt">li</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000087-2" xml:lang="zh-Hant">里</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000087-3" xml:lang="zh-Hans">里</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000087-4" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin">lǐ</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000087-5" xml:lang="zh-latn-wadegile">li</term>
            <note type="Gloss">
               <p xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000087-1">1. a ward (Steinhardt 1990, 227) or neighborhood (Miller 2007, 32) composed of multiple smaller units. In the <title ref="https://tinyurl.com/vjsw22mh">Zhouli 周禮</title> a li is a unit of 25 jia 家 ("households"), but this varies over time (e.g. 100 in the <term ref="/keyword/k000082">Tang dynasty</term>; 110 in the <term ref="/keyword/k000051">Ming dynasty</term>) (Hanyu dacidian; Kroll 2016, online edition); 2. a unit of length (Fu 2017, 360; Hanyu dacidian; Kroll 2016, online edition)</p>
               <p xml:lang="zh-Hant" source="#biblk000087-1">地方行政組織；一種長度單位。</p>
            </note>
